<% layout('/layouts/boilerplate') -%>

<!-- Introduction Section -->
<div class="plant-care-head-2">
    <section class="intro-section">
        <h1> <i class="fa-solid fa-seedling"></i>  Welcome to Plant Care Tips </h1>
    </section>
    <br><br>
    <br>
    <!-- Indoor Plants Section -->
    <section class="plant-care-section">
        <h2>---- Indoor Plants ----</h2>
        <br><br>
        <div class="plant-care-images">
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/snake.jpg" alt="Snake Plant" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Snake Plant</h3>
                <p>The Snake Plant thrives in low light and requires minimal water. Allow the soil to dry out completely between waterings. This hardy plant is perfect for beginners and adds a touch of greenery to any room.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/peacelily.jpg" alt="Peace Lily" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Peace Lily</h3>
                <p>Peace Lilies prefer low to medium light and need consistently moist soil. They can tolerate low light but bloom better in bright, indirect light. Keep the plant away from direct sunlight to avoid leaf burn.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/boston.jpg" alt="Boston Fern" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Boston Fern</h3>
                <p>Boston Ferns thrive in high humidity and indirect light. Keep the soil consistently moist but not waterlogged. This plant is perfect for bathrooms or other humid environments and adds a lush, green touch to indoor spaces.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Outdoor Plants Section -->
    <section class="plant-care-section">
        <h2>---- Outdoor Plants ----</h2>
        <br><br>
        <div class="plant-care-images">
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/tomato.jpg" alt="Tomato Plant" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Tomato Plant</h3>
                <p>Tomato plants need full sun and well-drained soil. Regular watering is required, especially during dry spells. Support the plants with stakes or cages as they grow to keep the fruit off the ground and reduce the risk of disease.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/sunflower.jpg" alt="Sunflower" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Sunflower</h3>
                <p>Sunflowers thrive in full sun and prefer well-drained soil. Water them regularly but allow the soil to dry out between waterings. They are drought-tolerant but will produce larger flowers with consistent moisture.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/carrot.jpg" alt="Carrot" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Carrot</h3>
                <p>Carrots need full sun and loose, well-drained soil to grow properly. Regular watering is essential, but avoid waterlogging the soil. They are easy to grow and provide a delicious, nutritious harvest.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Succulents Section -->
    <section class="plant-care-section">
        <h2>---- Succulents ----</h2>
        <br><br>
        <div class="plant-care-images">
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/aloevera.jpg" alt="Aloe Vera" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Aloe Vera</h3>
                <p>Aloe Vera prefers bright, indirect light and infrequent watering. The soil should be allowed to dry out completely between waterings. This succulent is known for its medicinal properties and is a great addition to any home.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/echeveria.jpg" alt="Echeveria" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Echeveria</h3>
                <p>Echeveria thrives in bright light and requires minimal watering. Use a well-draining soil mix to ensure the plant's roots do not sit in excess moisture. Its rosette shape and variety of colors make it a popular choice for succulent collections.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="plant-care-item">
                <img src="/images/cactus.jpg" alt="Cactus" class="plant-img">
                <h3>Cactus</h3>
                <p>Cacti are known for their ability to withstand dry conditions and high light. They require minimal watering, with the soil needing to dry out completely between waterings. Cacti are perfect for adding a unique touch to your plant collection.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>